==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Margosa
<hw>Mar*go"sa</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pg.
<ets>amargoso</ets> bitter.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A large tree
of the genus <gen>Melia</gen> (<spn>Melia Azadirachta</spn>) found in
India. Its bark is bitter, and used as a tonic. A valuable oil is
expressed from its seeds, and a tenacious gum exudes from its trunk. The
<spn>Melia Azedarach</spn> is a much more showy tree, and is cultivated
in the Southern United States, where it is known as <stype>Pride of
India</stype>, <stype>Pride of China</stype>, or <stype>bead
tree</stype>. Various parts of the tree are considered
anthelmintic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>margosa</qex> oil . . . is a most valuable balsam for
wounds, having a peculiar smell which prevents the attacks of flies.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir S. Baker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Margraviate</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Margravate</ent>⟦br⟧
